### Description

Considering this code:

```
constructor( private _fb: FormBuilder) {}

ngOnInit() {
  this.form = this._fb.group<{name: FormControl<string|null>}>({
    name: new FormControl(null),
  });
  
  // Below code should throw error but not.
  this.form.controls.name.setValue(1234); 
}
```

**Expected**: the form field `name` should be typed as `string` or `null`, and should show error when setting its value to any other types.
**Actual**:   `this.form.controls.name.setValue(1234);` succeed without any warnings

